<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="696" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/12–351: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Millard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-03T19:00:00+01:00">December
                                    3, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>770. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 778, Nov 27 and <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 755, Nov 30, rptd The Hague 44.
                                <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> note recd today requesting
                            immediate consultation on withdrawal of US concession on item 1520.
                            Please instruct.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Millard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>